// Muxr dev-rig zellij config.
//
// Intentionally minimal: zellij fills in its built-in defaults for every section
// we omit (keybinds, plugin aliases, themes, web client, …). The one thing we pin
// is an empty `load_plugins` block.
//
// zellij 0.44.3's bundled default config ships `load_plugins { "zellij:link" }` —
// a background plugin (makes terminal file-paths clickable) that loads on every
// new session and surfaced as a stray pane in app-created sessions. An explicit
// empty block keeps it — and any other background plugin — from loading.
//
// Installed by entrypoint.sh on every boot. The config dir (/root/.config/zellij)
// is a persisted named volume in compose.yaml, so a build-time COPY alone would
// only seed a fresh volume and miss pre-existing ones — hence the entrypoint
// (re)install.
load_plugins {
}
